<% layout("/layouts/boilerplate") -%>
<h1 class="text-center mt-2">Project Details</h1>
<div class="card mb-3 bg-transparent mt-3 mb-5">
  <img src="/images/InstagramNode.png" class="card-img-top rounded shadow w-75 mx-auto" alt="img">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h5 class="card-title text-center"><i class="fas fa-database"></i> CRUD Application (HTML, CSS & JavaScript)</h5>
    <p class="card-text text-center">“Understanding Data Flow Without a Database!”</p>
    <p class="card-text text-center">
      This project is a client-side CRUD application that performs Create, Read, Update, and Delete operations entirely in the browser. All data is managed dynamically using JavaScript arrays and DOM manipulation, making it a great exercise in handling application state without relying on a backend or database.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b> Key Features:</b>
      <ul>
        <li>Create: Add new entries through a form, instantly displayed on the page.</li>
        <li>Read: Render all stored data dynamically from an in-memory array.</li>
        <li>Update: Edit existing entries using index-based logic.</li>
        <li>Delete: Remove entries seamlessly and re-render the list in real time.</li>
        <li>Npm package: <strong>UUID</strong> package for unique id.</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>What I Learned:</b>
      <ul>
        <li> Managing data structures in JavaScript to simulate a database.</li>
        <li>Using DOM manipulation to reflect data changes on the UI.</li>
        <li>Writing modular functions to handle each operation efficiently.</li>
        <li>Building the foundation for full-stack CRUD by understanding client-side logic.</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>